HEADWORD: Jument
<hw>Ju"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>jumentum</ets> a beast of burden: cf. F. <ets>jument</ets> a mare,
OF., a beast of burden.]</ety> <def>A beast; especially, a beast of
burden.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fitter for <qex>juments</qex> than men to feed on.</q>
<rj><qau>Burton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

